            The other point is with regard to the comparison&#x2014;and I am interested in pursuing this because I believe it is an important point&#x2014;between land-based installations and ships. The point that I was trying to make is that the information is in a different category. It is not quite as meaningful as for land-based sources. You would not know for instance whether a ship had discharged at a different point, whereas a land-based installation of course is fixed and does not have the opportunities for disposal elsewhere that a ship has. I hope I have not
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_28gc' title='Col. 28GC &mdash; HL Deb 25 November 1996 vol 576 c28GC' name='column_28gc' href='#column_28gc' rel='bookmark'>28GC</a>
