      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00723'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961125_GCR_171' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 1 <span class="italic">[Amendments of <a href="/acts/merchant-shipping-act-1995">Merchant Shipping Act 1995</a> relating to inspection and detention of ships]:</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00724'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961125_GCR_172' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Viscount Goschen</span> moved Amendment No. 40:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00725'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961125_GCR_173' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 26, line 43, after ("a") insert ("qualifying").
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00726'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961125_GCR_174' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Viscount said: The purpose of the amendment is to correct a reference in Schedule 1 dealing with inspection and detention from "a foreign ship" to "a qualifying foreign ship". The distinction is necessary when referring to ships which are entitled to exercise the right of innocent and transit passage. The term "qualifying foreign ship" is defined in Schedule 6 of the Bill. I hope that the Committee will accept my explanation. This is very much a matter of drafting. I hope the Committee will feel able to accept the amendment. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00727'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0576P0_19961125_GCR_175' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0576P0-00728'>
